annotationA: Vacuolar protein sorting-associated protein 18 homolog; Required for the biogenesis of eye pigment granules. Plays a role in vesicle-mediated protein trafficking to lysosomal compartments and in membrane docking/fusion reactions of late endosomes/lysosomes. Required to maintain normal levels of rush, which functions in endosome formation and trafficking
annotationB: Syntaxin 13, isoform A; SNAP receptor activity; protein binding; SNARE binding. It is involved in the biological process described with: mitotic nuclear division; mitotic cytokinesis; meiosis I cytokinesis; male meiosis; vesicle-mediated transport; female meiotic division; synaptic vesicle docking involved in exocytosis; intracellular protein transport; vesicle fusion; neurotransmitter secretion; Belongs to the syntaxin family
